summary: The customer calls ITC to follow up on a complaint regarding a mistaken package in a packet of biscuits he bought. The customer wants to know if he can get a replacement. The customer care agent asks for the customer's whatsapp number to send him the company's official number to restart the whatsapp and check the number. The customer is then asked if he wants a replacement. The customer explains the nature of his complaint and the agent promises to look into the matter. The agent offers the customer a goodwill gesture of a replacement pack. The customer accepts. The agent then asks for the customer's location so that an executive can come and replace the packet with a sample. The customer sends photos of the incorrect item and is told to mention the complaint number when sending the photos. The customer is then asked if he needs anything else.
speaker_a_summary: The user calls ITC to complain about a mistake in the packaging of their product. They bought a packet that was supposed to weigh 430 rupees but was overpriced at 650 rupees. They also mention that the weight of the product was less than the advertised weight and that they spent 60 rupees per day on this purchase. They ask for a replacement but the customer service agent avoids giving a clear answer. The user gets agitated and explains that they buy in bulk but this package was a low standard compared to the others. They also explain that the weight of the product was not right and that there is a difference of 37 grams from the correct weight. The user ends the call by giving their contact number again for the customer agent to send them the right information about the complaint.
speaker_b_summary: The customer, Mister Ramilangala, is in a dispute with a company regarding their product. The agent tries to resolve the issue by requesting that Mister Ramilangala restarts their phone and checks their Whatsapp number, as well as provides an email as a means for further assistance. The agent also informs Mister Ramilangala that they will need to provide a sample of the product in order to proceed with any potential replacements. The agent later asks Mister Ramilangala for details regarding their weight machine and the weight of the packets they have been producing, as well as asks for a photo of the issue.
cohere_points:
- Customer is frustrated with agent over replacement of incorrect product.
- Customer complaints about different packages of biscuits bought.
- Customer discusses the wrong packages with many representatives.
- Agent asks for photos of the products to be sent through WhatsApp.
- Agent will check for internal repairs and replace the packets.
